	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.34]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Crystalline silk can be obtained off of spiders in Crystal Caverns, and off of the spiders in Thurgadin.&nbsp;&nbsp;There may be other places you can get them, but these are easy spots.<br><br>The vial is not trivial at 119 skill in pottery, but I've made it many times without failure at that skill.<br><br>The gate is not instant cast and takes a few seconds.  But the vial does not vanish immediately during the cast, so I'd expect that if the cast were interrupted the vial would still be in your inventory.<br><br>This is very easy to get once you have the pottery skill (you can master pottery in a couple hours at not too much cost).  My monk carries this around all the time now, and keeps several unfired vials in the bank so that he can make another one immediately upon using one.<br><br>It gates you to a relatively safe point in Thurgadin, so even if you are KOS there, your gate is fine.  However, if you are KOS there, it's hard to make this item, as you need a container from an NPC in Thurgadin to make the final combine.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
